_sText: This map was inspired by gg_deagle_5 and aim_shotty intended for gungame.  Therefore I cant take total credit for this map.  However I thought the two maps combined in the right way would make for allot of fun.  I did not decompile any maps for this, I just went by memory and also by looking at the maps, so Im sure the dimensions are not to the correct standards of the two maps.  I added different textures to spice things up a little.  I did not go into great detail on this map because I wanted something that played good and would give good fps.  I used Hammer, 20 players and nav file.

gg_bkh_roundabout_1
This is a medium sized map I made for Gungame, but I did include buyzones because this map doubles as a nice Deathmatch map also. It is somewhat of a fightyard layout but it does have a tunnel system that circles around the entire lower portion of the map. There are three different levels. You can excess the top of the buildings via ladders and each building has its own tunnel entrance with four other tunnel exits/entrances from the center yard area. Added features below
  • 36 spawnpoints
  • Ambient Sounds
  • 3D skybox
  • Displacements
  • Buyzones
  • Custom texturs
  • Cables/wires
Note:
If you want to do an assessment, I know that "Internet Explorer" works. I'm not sure Firefox will work. Also I am aware of some of the textures not quite lining up in the tunnel area, but once the brushes have been stretched and skewed its seems impossible to get the textures to line up properly. So if anyone has any information on how to fix this please feel free to send that info my way. I'm open to all constructive criticism.

gg_bkh_mole_fThis is a map I made a while back and decided to release it with updated textures and also several modifications. I created this map with the idea of an underground tunnel system. The map is about 98% displacements. Players start out in a tunnel like cavern and there are two ways to exit the spawn. One exit leads to the upper level and the other exit leads to the lower level. Once you make your way out of the spawns there is an open area that consists of two levels. This is where most of the action will take place. Included are a couple of rope ladders, nav file, buyzones, sound, and 32 players. Please download before assessing. I enhanced the screenshot for better viewing, so the screenshots are a bit brighter than the actual map. Any constructive criticism would be appreciated.

UpdatesThanks to my fellow mappers assessments and their keen eyes and knowledge for mapping details, I have updated this map with the following.
  • Softened the lighting so it is not as bright.
  • Created more of a rougher look on the tunnel walls so they dont look so round.
  • Added a generator with sound and also added cables/wires and light switches for the lighting.
  • Replaced the track texture with metal grate texture.
  • more displacement work on the center floor area.
Thanks again for all the constructive feedback.
Underground action.  Includes teleport and rope ladders.  A tunnel system that leads to the center war zone.  20 players max and includes a nav file.  I use it on Dm server and map get good fps.

-= NEED SOME HELP =- 

I'm adding this map so people can assess it and give me feedback on how I can improve the optimization portion of this map.  I'm not happy with the file size and I need some experience mappers to critique the heck out of it.  I'm probably going to add a 3D skybox.  Its hard to use skip,hint and func_areaportal in the doorways and windows because everything is round and I know to use them they have to fit the opening just right.  So I need so advice from you mappers out there.

-= MAP DESCRIPTION =-

This map contains 5 portals on each side.  1 on top of each castle for a quick way down to original spawn point.  2 on each second floor for a quick way to the top of the castle, (screenshot 3) and 2 semi-secret portals behind the spiral stairway castle, (screenshot 1 you can see the arrows in the corner of the map), that takes you to the top of the opponents castle.  Map is very playable but I"m just not quite happy with the end results.  

Also includes rope ladders and land mines.  2 spiral staircases in each tower.  On the top of each castle is a cannon that shoots barrels to the other teams castle by pressing the red button in screen shot 6.  

I'm open to all constructive criticism and would like some feedback on how to improve this map.  

Max 20 players and did not include a nav file because I will probably be making so changes.

Thanks guys.

This is a really fun map.  Has teleports and lots of ramps that eject you to either side of the map and land in water.  I use it on my Dm gg server.  Alot of action.  3D skybox, 20 player max, no nav file due to the teleports and ramps.

One of the favorites on my server.  It playes very well.  Lots of ladders and oneway glass.  Includes 3D skybow and dust motes.  Nothing fancy just good game play and fun. Oh yea, Has 2 fish tanks, lol.  0 players max.

I made this map to have kind of a Halo look.  Players can move through this map very smoothly.  Lots of ramps and ladders that flow from one another.  It has a 4 story free fall into water through a tunnel from the top to the bottom for a quick way down if you dont want to use the ladders.  I also implemented a toxic area on the top so players cant set up camp.  They can get a couple kills but will have to move on or die.  Extremely fun and built for great fps.  Map can also be used for other cs.s games other than just gg.  20 players max, and no nav file due to all the different levels.

and adding a new skybox.  Also added two more spawn

This is a map I created for my gg server.

Note: Nothing fancy here.  No arches, rounded corners
or anything that would hinder fps.  This map was built
as simple as possible to promote a high quality of
gameplay but yet tried to give the map an appealing
side also.
Strategically placed crates and designed for close quarters
gameplay and also a few sniping spots.

I did a test run on my server and players really liked the
way they were able to maneuver smoothly and freely from
one area to another.  Makes for a fun round of fragging.  

----------------------------------------------------

Open to all constructive criticism.

This is a gungame map I created for my server.  The setting is down in a valley and the theme was made to have a fort look.  
This is a symmetrical map for even teamplay and each home base has 3 floors that are accessible by ladders. 
The map includes a 3D skybox and there are 34 spawn points. 
There is also a nav file included. 
I'm open to all constructive criticism.

This is another "bkh" map that I made and run on my server.  I use it for GG/DM but I also included buy zones so it can be use as a non GG map.  

----------------------------------------

This map includes two bottle neck tunnels in the center with a red smoke screen in the center of each tunnel so obscure the opponents and includes a whoosh sound when entering the smoke.  I also included several optimizing tools such as Tools/Hint, Tools/Skip, Tools/Nodraw, Tools/Block Light  and Tools/Occulder.  
There is also many displacements used for the columns and curved objects.  A Nav file is included.  This map has 42 spawn points, 21 on each side.  It is not a random spawn map. 

----------------------------------------

NOTE:
I play this map on my server but there has been a couple players that claim they see purple where the blue should be.  I'm not sure why this is.  Ive only had this complaint from 2 players.  Everyone else sees  it just the way it looks in the screen shots.  So if anyone know why this might be happening please pass it on to me.  I personally believe its their video card but I just wanted to let people know.

----------------------------------------

UPDATE

The blue texture has been changed/fixed due to some players could not DL the texture.

----------------------------------------
  

I'm open to all constructive criticism and any suggestions to make this a better map.

gg_bkh_dead_end_1
This is a gungame map that I made with a dead end street setting. The map has the main street where most of the action will take place, but it also includes two hallways, one on each side of the map, so players will have more options to sneak up on the enemy. We play this on my gungame server and the clan seems to really like it. The buildings and street at the opposite end of the tunnel is all part of the 3D skybox. Below is a list of included items.
  • 3D custom skybox
  • Custom textures
  • Custom props.
  • smoke stack.
  • Optimized with skip and hint tools.
  • 36 spawn points
  • Nav file
All constructive criticism welcome.

This is a super fun map, especially for DM.  The middle area is surrounded by a moat of water and you teleport from your spawn to 5 different locations on the map.  No spawn killing in this map because players cant see where the players spawn from.  It has 3 different levels with ladders from the water to the top.  20 players max, no nav file because of all the teleports and ladders and underwater action.

This is kind of an assault/fightyard map I use for gungame on my server.  Map includes a 3D skybox, many ladders, arched columns to hold up the structure and alot of stairs.  Its really a fun map.  The teams spawn  on opposite sides, its not a random spawn.  Spawns are pretty well protected from spawn killers.  Indoor & outdoor play area.  I was really pleased with the way the skybox lined up.  The road looks as if its part of the map the way it extends into the 3D area.  Max of 24 players, and also includes a nav file.  I'm open to all constructive criticism.

This map was made for gungame. Its a basic map that was intended to give high performance during gameplay. Players spawn on the middle and lower floors. The map includes 40 spawn points. Contains nav file. I'm open to all constructive criticism.
